# Feature Spec: App Version Placement

## 1. Summary
Move the visible app version from the native menu/app-name label into the app/window name so users see `GoThru Photo Studio <version>` as the application title, while the native menu label stays clean as `GoThru Photo Studio` on every supported OS.

## 2. Problem
The current shell presents the version beside the first app/menu label, as shown in the reference screenshot: `GoThru Photo Studio 1.1.1` appears before `File`, `Edit`, `View`, `Settings`, `Window`, and `Help`. This makes the menu row feel cluttered and OS-inconsistent.

## 3. Goal
- Show the app version as part of the app/window name.
- Remove the app version from the native menu/app-name label.
- Keep behavior consistent on Windows, macOS, and Linux.
- Use the app's configured version as the single source of truth.

## 4. User Story
As a GoThru Photo Studio user, I want the version to appear in the app name/title area instead of inside the menu row, so the menu remains clean while the running version is still visible.

## 5. Requirements

### Functional Requirements
- The displayed app/window title must use the format `GoThru Photo Studio <version>`.
- The version must be read from the app metadata/configuration, not hardcoded in the UI or menu builder.
- The native menu/app-name label must display only `GoThru Photo Studio`.
- The menu items after the app-name label must remain unchanged: `File`, `Edit`, `View`, `Settings`, `Window`, `Help`.
- The About/update flows may continue to show version information where they already do; this change only moves the version out of the menu label.

### Platform Requirements
- Windows: the title bar/taskbar window title should show `GoThru Photo Studio <version>`; the menu label should not include the version.
- macOS: the application menu name should remain `GoThru Photo Studio`; the window title should show `GoThru Photo Studio <version>` where the OS displays document/window title text.
- Linux: the window title should show `GoThru Photo Studio <version>`; app/menu labels should not duplicate the version.

### Non-Functional Requirements
- No new localization keys are required for the product name or version string.
- The implementation must not change update logic, bundle versioning, installer metadata, or release signing.
- The implementation must tolerate version changes without requiring code edits.

## 6. Current Code Anchors
- App metadata: `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json` -> `productName`, `version`.
- Main window title: `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json` -> `app.windows[].title`.
- Native menu/system shell: existing App Shell migration area, especially menu construction referenced in `docs/migration/features/app-shell.md`.
- Package metadata: `package.json` -> `version`; must stay aligned with Tauri version if both are used by build/release tooling.

## 7. Proposed Implementation Notes
- Prefer deriving the title from Tauri package metadata at runtime or build time, using `productName` + `version`.
- If Tauri config cannot interpolate version directly in `app.windows[].title`, set the title during setup/startup from the Rust side.
- Keep menu construction separate from title construction. Menu labels should use product name only.
- Avoid copying the screenshot's version value (`1.1.1`) into source; it is an example, not a requirement.

## 8. Acceptance Criteria
- Given app version `1.1.1`, the visible app/window title reads `GoThru Photo Studio 1.1.1`.
- Given the native menu is visible, the first app/menu label reads `GoThru Photo Studio` with no version suffix.
- Given the user opens `File`, `Edit`, `View`, `Settings`, `Window`, or `Help`, the existing menu structure and actions still work.
- Given the app version changes for a release, the app/window title reflects the new version without editing menu labels.
- Verified on Windows, macOS, and Linux, or documented with screenshots for any OS not available during QA.

## 9. Out of Scope
- Redesigning the native menu.
- Changing About modal copy or update notification copy.
- Changing release version numbers.
- Changing installer product name, bundle identifier, or package metadata beyond the title display.

## 10. QA Checklist
- Capture before/after screenshots of the app shell on each OS.
- Confirm no menu label contains a version string.
- Confirm the app/window title includes the current version.
- Confirm About/update version display remains unchanged.
- Confirm automated build still reads the same configured app version.

## 11. Priority
MoSCoW: Must Have.

RICE estimate:
- Reach: high, visible to all desktop users.
- Impact: low to medium, improves polish and consistency.
- Confidence: high.
- Effort: xs to s, depending on whether title interpolation is supported directly or must be set in startup code.

## 12. Status
Not started.
